[1
Date: Wed, 27 Oct 1999 08:55:20 -0400
From: David Waltner-Toews <dwaltner@uoguelph.ca>

I have been on a lot of aeroplanes which are sprayed with passengers
inside. I am less concerned about side-effects or long term effects, which
for sporadic exposure like that are likely to be minimal. I am more
concerned that this is a cosmetic activity which lulls North Americans and
Europeans into the impression that we don't really have to spend serious
money, energy, and research time working with tropical countries to come up
with sustainable solutions to their disease problems.
Is there any published research which demonstrates that this spraying
actually "works"?
--
David Waltner-Toews
Department of Population Medicine
University of Guelph
e-mail: dwaltner@uoguelph.ca
